<br>
First of all the AA points may make these fights easier, but that is why we are working our ass off to get them. Adjustment by mobs is ridiculous. Why doesn't Dvinn in Crushbone adjust to lvl 60 players also and starts DTing the zone? Instead of making the old and boring @#%$ more difficult, VI should show their hands and open up Vex Thal. I am sure that nobody will even think about wasting time in NToV once the Luclin UBER-@#%$ is available. Besides that this game is moving in waves. Everyone climbed the latter from Crushbone to Unrest to CT to Guk to Sol B to KC to Sebilis.....and the lower levels followed. It is time for 'others' to go to NToV now while the 'high end' guilds should be allowed to move on to Vex Thal!<br>
<br>
This was about the change in general. Now to specific things. Aary got harder, ok cool, we still kill him! On our server only two guilds were able to kill him before the patch and the very same guilds can still kill him after the patch. So does this change make sense?<br>
All other mobs are pushovers now though. Look at these perma-rooted mobs! You cannot mess up the pull and train them on your casters because they don't move. There is still room to hide from AEs. Their aggro is so low that you could ride their back and take photos for the album. These mobs got gimpified to beeing MEGAwhimps.<br>
We cleared ToV before and after the change and everyone agreed that all permarooted mobs are a joke now.<br>
<br>
The Vulak script is simply @#%$ also. Whoever came up with this warp/depopp @#%$ should be fired. Mobs who have someone on the hate list should not depopp. Then there is way too much random factor on the spawns. You can have a spawn with a CHing wurm and 4 healer drakes. What is this? AE heals like RoF? Oh yeah...targetted towards Luclin abilities! Too bad paladin silence has been taken out of the game. Do the designers know about this front-office-decision already? Maybe they know it and want us to use the new abilities like 'flesh to bone' or maybe the sense heading +15% item from Grieg does the trick! Maybe they want us to do AE groups in there...someone explain please!! <br>
<br>
I want screenshots from the in-the-house-testserver where 60 VI employees work through that whole script and spawn Vulak. Hey, I know they did NOT test it, because they don't even have 60 guys in this company who are still playing this game!<br>
<br>
They want to force us to do the exp-mill to get AA points, so that they can collect cash for the subscription. Ok, that's granted, but at the same time I am lacking motivation to work my ass off to be able to kill the very SAME mobs again, that I used to own a couple of months ago. This is wrong! How about a new challence with new zones? <br>
<br>
And last but not least, killing Tunare with a fully spawned zone was a kickass operation. Now this challenge has been taken out of the game also and was replaced with 'clear-the-whole-@#%$-until-your-face-turns-blue'-crap again. Yeah, make us spend 10 hours killing thriflings with 1-zillion hps! That's my definition of fun!<br>
<br>
Neric the Heretic<br>
